---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import TopBar from "../components/TopBar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import NpmInstall from "../components/NpmInstall.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <TopBar />

  <main>
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pt-24 pb-28 md:pt-32 md:pb-36">
      <h1
        class="font-display text-[clamp(2.5rem,6.2vw,4.75rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.04] tracking-[-0.01em] text-ink"
      >
        The 2D Game Engine<br />for your AI Agent
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-[54ch] font-body text-[1.15rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">
        You have the game idea — your AI can build it with Hayao. Designed specifically for
        AI-native gamedev, with a focus on fun &amp; fast prototyping. Fully free &amp; open source.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="/play"
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg bg-orange px-5 py-3 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-semibold text-white no-underline transition-colors hover:bg-green"
        >
          Playground
        </a>
        <NpmInstall />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 1 · AI-NATIVE ── -->
    <section class="border-t border-hair">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl items-center gap-12 px-6 py-24 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-16 md:py-28">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-4 font-body text-[0.75rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-orange">AI-native</p>
          <h2 class="text-balance font-display text-[clamp(1.85rem,3.4vw,2.6rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.01em] text-ink">
            Built for the machine that writes the game
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 max-w-[48ch] font-body text-[1.05rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">
            Godot, GameMaker and Unity are made for humans clicking through an editor — GUIs,
            binary scene files, a bespoke language. An agent can't diff a
            <code class="rounded bg-[#f2f3f6] px-1 font-mono text-[0.85em] text-ink">.tscn</code>
            it can't read. Hayao keeps Godot's proven model — nodes, scenes, signals — but makes
            every part <span class="text-ink">text, typed and greppable</span>. The whole game is
            code your AI can write, read back, and reason about.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-hair">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 text-[0.92rem]">
            <div class="border-r border-hair bg-[#f8f9fb] p-6">
              <p class="mb-4 font-body text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-muted">Traditional engine</p>
              <ul class="space-y-3 font-body font-light text-soft">
                <li>GUI &amp; binary scenes</li>
                <li>Runs only inside the app</li>
                <li>“Looks right?” — open it</li>
                <li>Opaque to an LLM</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6">
              <p class="mb-4 font-body text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-green">Hayao</p>
              <ul class="space-y-3 font-body font-light text-ink">
                <li>Plain TypeScript, greppable</li>
                <li>Runs headless in Node</li>
                <li>Assert on state, prove it</li>
                <li>Every symbol is text</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 2 · DETERMINISTIC ── -->
    <section class="border-t border-hair">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24 md:py-28">
        <div class="grid items-center gap-12 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-16">
          <div>
            <p class="mb-4 font-body text-[0.75rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-blue">Deterministic</p>
            <h2 class="text-balance font-display text-[clamp(1.85rem,3.4vw,2.6rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.01em] text-ink">
              The game is a pure function of its inputs
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-5 max-w-[48ch] font-body text-[1.05rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">
              Every frame is <span class="text-ink">state → step(inputs) → state</span>. All
              randomness flows through one seeded RNG; there is no wall-clock and no hidden state.
              Same inputs, same result — bit for bit, on any machine. That one guarantee is where
              the superpowers come from.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-hair bg-[#0f1424] p-6">
            <pre class="font-mono text-[0.85rem] leading-relaxed text-[#d7dcec]"><code><span class="text-[#8ea1c7]">const</span> w = createWorld(game);
w.step([<span class="text-[#9cc98a]">'right'</span>]);      <span class="text-[#6b769b]">// advance one tick</span>
w.step([]);             <span class="text-[#6b769b]">// release — next input</span>

w.probe().solved;       <span class="text-[#6b769b]">// assert on STATE, not pixels</span>
<span class="text-[#8ea1c7]">const</span> h = w.hash();    <span class="text-[#6b769b]">// replay later → same hash, or it's a bug</span></code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-16 grid gap-x-10 gap-y-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <div>
            <div class="mb-2 h-1 w-8 rounded-full bg-green"></div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-[1.05rem] font-semibold text-ink">Prove it works</h3>
            <p class="mt-1.5 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">Run in Node, assert on state. No browser, no pixels, no flakiness.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="mb-2 h-1 w-8 rounded-full bg-green"></div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-[1.05rem] font-semibold text-ink">Prove it's winnable</h3>
            <p class="mt-1.5 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">step() is a pure transition, so a solver can search every level to the end.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="mb-2 h-1 w-8 rounded-full bg-blue"></div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-[1.05rem] font-semibold text-ink">Refactor without fear</h3>
            <p class="mt-1.5 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">Replay the input log, compare the hash. Identical, or you just found a regression.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="mb-2 h-1 w-8 rounded-full bg-blue"></div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-[1.05rem] font-semibold text-ink">Time-travel &amp; undo</h3>
            <p class="mt-1.5 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">snapshot() and restore() any tick. Undo and save-states fall out for free.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="mb-2 h-1 w-8 rounded-full bg-orange"></div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-[1.05rem] font-semibold text-ink">Replays &amp; scrubbing</h3>
            <p class="mt-1.5 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">A whole session is just its input log — jump to any moment and re-simulate forward.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="mb-2 h-1 w-8 rounded-full bg-orange"></div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-[1.05rem] font-semibold text-ink">Rollback multiplayer</h3>
            <p class="mt-1.5 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">Determinism is exactly what makes lockstep and rollback netcode possible at all.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 3 · SCENE TREE ── -->
    <section class="border-t border-hair">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl items-center gap-12 px-6 py-24 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-16 md:py-28">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-4 font-body text-[0.75rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-green">Scene tree</p>
          <h2 class="text-balance font-display text-[clamp(1.85rem,3.4vw,2.6rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.01em] text-ink">
            Godot's scene tree, in plain code
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 max-w-[48ch] font-body text-[1.05rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">
            Compose your game from nodes — the model Godot got right. Node2D, Sprite, Camera2D,
            Timer, AnimationPlayer and behaviours: a tree you build in TypeScript, not a binary you
            edit in a GUI. Rendering is just a projection of that tree, so the simulation never
            needs a canvas to run.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-hair bg-[#f8f9fb] p-6">
          <pre class="font-mono text-[0.9rem] leading-relaxed text-muted"><code>World
└─ <span class="text-blue">Node2D</span> <span class="text-ink">player</span>
   ├─ <span class="text-blue">Sprite</span> <span class="text-ink">body</span>
   ├─ <span class="text-blue">Camera2D</span> <span class="text-ink">follow</span>
   ├─ <span class="text-blue">AnimationPlayer</span> <span class="text-ink">run</span>
   └─ <span class="text-blue">Timer</span> <span class="text-ink">coyote</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 4 · OPEN SOURCE (navy band) ── -->
    <section class="bg-navy">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24 text-center md:py-28">
        <p class="mb-4 font-body text-[0.75rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-orange">Free &amp; open source</p>
        <h2 class="mx-auto max-w-[20ch] text-balance font-display text-[clamp(1.85rem,3.6vw,2.8rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.01em] text-white">
          MIT-licensed. Yours to jam with.
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-[58ch] font-body text-[1.1rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-white/70">
          No seats, no runtime fees, no strings. <code class="font-mono text-white">npm i hayao</code>{" "}
          and you're building. Winnability and determinism are proven before your deadline, and the
          whole engine is text your agent already speaks — perfect for a weekend jam.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/hellojanpacan/hayao-js"
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg bg-orange px-5 py-3 font-body text-[0.95rem] font-semibold text-white no-underline transition-colors hover:bg-green"
          >
            Star on GitHub
          </a>
          <NpmInstall tone="light" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 5 · ASSETS AS CODE ── -->
    <section class="border-t border-hair">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl items-center gap-12 px-6 py-24 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-16 md:py-28">
        <div class="order-2 md:order-1 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-hair">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 360 210" class="w-full" role="img" aria-label="Vector art drawn from code">
            <rect width="360" height="210" fill="#ffffff"></rect>
            <circle cx="280" cy="62" r="28" fill="#e59500"></circle>
            <path d="M0 150 Q90 108 180 140 T360 132 V210 H0 Z" fill="#669bbc"></path>
            <path d="M0 176 Q110 138 220 170 T360 164 V210 H0 Z" fill="#337357"></path>
            <rect x="150" y="120" width="14" height="14" rx="3" fill="#29335c"></rect>
          </svg>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 border-t border-hair px-5 py-3">
            <span class="flex gap-1.5">
              <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-green"></span>
              <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-navy"></span>
              <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-orange"></span>
              <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-blue"></span>
            </span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[0.8rem] text-muted">drawn in code → rendered to SVG / Canvas</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
          <p class="mb-4 font-body text-[0.75rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-blue">Assets as code</p>
          <h2 class="text-balance font-display text-[clamp(1.85rem,3.4vw,2.6rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.01em] text-ink">
            Art your agent can actually make
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 max-w-[48ch] font-body text-[1.05rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-soft">
            An AI can't paint a PNG — but it can write vectors. Hayao's art is code: palettes,
            shapes, procedural textures, bitmap fonts and autotiling, all rendered crisp to SVG or
            Canvas. No binary sprite sheets to source, nothing the agent can't produce. And the look
            is cosmetic and deterministic — it paints the state, it never changes it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
